Package org.jsapar.model Description

The canonical data model used by this library.

A Document contains multiple Line objects where each line corresponds to a line of the input buffer. Within each Line there are multiple Cell objects that correspond to fields or items on each line within the input.

You can use this model to build a structure that you later compose to an output by using a Composer.

While using a ParseTask, this model will be the result, either as separate Line objects in LineEvent or as a complete Document. In order to make it easier to retrieve and alter cell values within a Line, you may use the LineUtils class.
